### Create a new book

**HTTP POST** request to {{baseURL}}books.

#### Request Body

- { "title": "{{$randomWord}}", "author": "{{$randomFullName}}", "isbn": "{{$randomInt}}-{{$randomInt}}- ...", "releaseDate": "{{$isoTimestamp}}"}


#### Response

The response of this request can be documented as a JSON schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "title": {"type": "string"},
    "author": {"type": "string"},
    "isbn": {"type": "string"},
    "releaseDate": {"type": "string"},
    "createdAt": {"type": "string"},
    "updatedAt": {"type": "string"},
    "id": {"type": "integer"}
  }
}

 ```

### Retrieve all households

#### Request

This is a `GET` request to the endpoint `{{baseURL}}households` to retrieve all households.

#### Response

The response for this request is a JSON array containing household objects. Each household object has the following properties:

- `name` (string): The name of the household.

- `createdAt` (string): The timestamp when the household was created.

- `updatedAt` (string): The timestamp when the household was last updated.

- `id` (number): The unique identifier for the household.

- `links` (array): An array of link objects containing `rel` (string) and `href` (string) properties.


#### JSON Schema

``` json
{
  "type": "array",
  "items": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "name": { "type": "string" },
      "createdAt": { "type": "string" },
      "updatedAt": { "type": "string" },
      "id": { "type": "number" },
      "links": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "rel": { "type": "string" },
            "href": { "type": "string" }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

